                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; two groups of lines on the incipit page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; name of Hebrew letter in Ps. 118 (fol. 32ra); abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 3vb, 4ra), nǝbäl (e.g., fols. 4rb, 5rb), halle luya (e.g., fols. 5vb, 6ra), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 33rb, 36rb), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 33vb, 46vb), mǝʿrāf (fol. 49vb).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="3ra" to="113vb">3ra-113vb</locus> (quires I-XIV); the handwriting remains uniform throughout the Ms. and is characterized by finely shaped and slightly right-sloping letters. It shows Gondarine influence. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Hand b: <locus from="115ra" to="130vb">115ra-130vb</locus> (quires XV-XVII); rounded and small letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
